Observation Details: It is almost impossible for me to note Redheads, thanks to color-blindness. Nevertheless, I saw one female bird that looked like a female Scaup but lacked the white front and had a round head. I think this was a Redhead.
Hundreds for one large raft; three more rafts.
1 female. Steep forehead and a smaller bill, with mostly yellow. Wish I had been able to get a photo, but I didn't locate it again.
